Package com.ibm.streams.management.job

Interface PeOutputPortMXBean

All Superinterfaces:
PePortMXBean
public interface PeOutputPortMXBean extends PePortMXBean
PeOutputPortMXBean provides attributes and operations for managing a processing element (PE) output port of a Streams job.

Note: The job must be registered before accessing any of these attributes or operations. See InstanceMXBean.registerJob(BigInteger) for more information.

ObjectNameBuilder.peOutputPort(String, String, BigInteger, int) can be used to build the ObjectName for a PeOutputPortMXBean.

The JobMXBean snapshot and PeMXBean snapshot operations provide an option to include attributes of descendant objects in the generated snapshot. If the value of the maximumDepth parameter identifies PE output port attributes should be included in the snapshot, the JSON format of the PE output port information returned is described in the product documentation. See topic: REST management API reference > Get PE output port. The following differences exist for the JMX output:

  • The REST specific properties: resourceType, restid, and self are not included.
  • The related job, and pe attributes are not repeated for the PE output port.
  • The metrics, property is not included.
  • The connections property is only included if the maximumDepth parameter on the submit call indicates it should be included. The value for this property is an embedded array containing snapshot objects for each optional connection of the PE input port. It includes both required and optional connections. For the format of these objects, see: PeConnectionMXBean.
